abstract: His placement behind his leading rivals in the caucuses on Monday dealt a damaging blow to his campaign. Some party officials say it was a long time in the works.
snippet: His placement behind his leading rivals in the caucuses on Monday dealt a damaging blow to his campaign. Some party officials say it was a long time in the works.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Maybe it was the threat of bad weather. Maybe it was a seating assignment debacle. Maybe it was a struggling campaign organization that still hadn’t found its footing.

abstract: The British government is questioning the BBC’s public funding and even picking fights with papers that have backed Prime Minister Boris Johnson with gusto.
snippet: The British government is questioning the BBC’s public funding and even picking fights with papers that have backed Prime Minister Boris Johnson with gusto.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — When Prime Minister Boris Johnson delivered a fireside chat last week to mark Britain’s departure from the European Union, he did not ask the BBC to tape it, preferring to use an in-house video crew. The BBC, in turn, refused to air his remarks on that history-making evening.

abstract: Comedians have always been tempted to make fun of tragedies, but a new controversy exposes how dark humor has evolved and expanded.
snippet: Comedians have always been tempted to make fun of tragedies, but a new controversy exposes how dark humor has evolved and expanded.
lead_paragraph: On the day of Kobe Bryant’s death, the comic Ari Shaffir wrote this on Twitter: “Kobe Bryant died 23 years too late today. He got away with rape because all the Hollywood liberals who attack comedy enjoy rooting for the Lakers more than they dislike rape. Big ups to the hero who forgot to gas up his chopper. I hate the Lakers. What a great day!”

abstract: Authors describe what it was like to work with the legendary Simon & Schuster editor, who died on Feb. 4.
snippet: Authors describe what it was like to work with the legendary Simon & Schuster editor, who died on Feb. 4.
lead_paragraph: The editor Alice Mayhew died on Tuesday at 87, leaving behind a legacy of best sellers and award-winning books. Some of the authors she worked with shared their memories of her.

abstract: The Trump administration’s decision to eventually withdraw several thousand troops from America’s longest war has triggered a debate within the 29-country alliance.
snippet: The Trump administration’s decision to eventually withdraw several thousand troops from America’s longest war has triggered a debate within the 29-country alliance.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Some members of the North Atlantic Treaty Organization are considering withdrawing thousands of their forces from Afghanistan once the United States begins to officially cut its own presence in the country, according to American and European officials.

abstract: President Trump was cleared of both impeachment charges. Only Mitt Romney crossed party lines, the lone Republican who voted to convict and remove the president from office.
snippet: President Trump was cleared of both impeachment charges. Only Mitt Romney crossed party lines, the lone Republican who voted to convict and remove the president from office.
lead_paragraph: The Senate acquitted President Trump on Wednesday of charges that he abused his power and obstructed Congress, as Republicans turned back an election-year attempt by House Democrats to remove him from office for pressuring a foreign power to incriminate his political rivals.

abstract: The president’s speech was jammed with engineered moments and sweeps stunts — and then came a cable-drama rip.
snippet: The president’s speech was jammed with engineered moments and sweeps stunts — and then came a cable-drama rip.
lead_paragraph: It’s no secret that Donald Trump, just months before he ran for the job of most powerful man in the world, was hosting Season 7 of “The Celebrity Apprentice.” But not all his TV appearances as president have been as reality-fied as one might have expected, especially his sedate, from-the-TelePrompTer State of the Union speeches.
